                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13551006" author="krummas" created="Fri, 11 Jan 2013 09:35:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch for this against trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13551579" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 11 Jan 2013 22:16:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My initial reaction was that I&apos;d prefer to manage the buffering explicitly instead of relying on nagle to get it right, but on further thought, I don&apos;t think it matters much: if the connection is busy, nagle will send out packets as soon as max segment size is reached; if it is not, then worst case 200-500ms delay from delayed ack is still tolerable if we are not treating cross-dc requests synchronously.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed defaulting to true for 1.2.1 and to false for 2.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
